   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>A Repentant Believer Having a Willing Spirit</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>In Psalm 51:12 David said to the Lord, "Restore unto me the joy of thy salvation, and uphold me with a willing spirit" ASV .</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>As a believer we should always have a willing spirit for the things of the Lord and for the things of the church.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Often, however, we are not willing in the things regarding the Lord's interest.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>We must be poor in spirit and willing in the things of the Lord's interest.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>DO YOU THINK THAT YOU HAVE THE SPIRIT OF GOD?</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In 1 Corinthians 7 Paul expresses a number of points concerning marriage.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Then in verse 40 he says, "But I think that I also have the Spirit of God."</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The Spirit of God here is the indwelling Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>A Normal Believer Having the Spirit of Joy</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>A normal believer should have the Spirit of joy Heb 1:9; Acts 13:52; Rom 14:17 .</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>We should have the Spirit of God in a joyful way.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The Spirit of God is the oil of joy Isa 61:1; Heb 1:9 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Therefore, we must be happy people, joyful all day long.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>We should be able to give thanks to God in everything Eph 5:20; Col 3:17 .</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>A God-fearing Person Having</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>the Spirit of Wisdom and Understanding,</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>the Spirit of Counsel and Might,</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>the Spirit of Knowledge and the Fear of God</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>A God-fearing person should have the Spirit of wisdom and understanding, the Spirit of counsel and might, the Spirit of knowledge and the fear of God Isa 11:2-3 .</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>If you have the Spirit of God, you must realize that the Spirit has many aspects.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The Spirit is full of wisdom and instruction, full of counsel and might.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Counsel refers to the way to do the right thing, and might refers to the strength to do the right thing.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The Spirit is also the Spirit of knowledge and the fear of God.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Isaiah joins knowledge and the fear of the Lord together.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Only the fear of God keeps us from being lawless.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>We must have the fear of the Lord and knowledge.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The more knowledge we have, the more fear of God we should have.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>If you are a person who has the Spirit of God, you will be wise, full of understanding, and full of instruction.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>You will also be a person who always has the proper way and the strength to carry things out.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>As a person who has the Spirit of God, you will not be a foolish or careless person, not fearing God.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Instead, you will be very knowledgeable, yet full of the fear of God.</S>
   </TEXT>
